“See How E.V. Road Trips Went From Impossible to Easy is an article in the New York Times comparing the evolution of electric cars and the charging stations throughout the USA regarding long-distance travel. The first graphic, an interactive map, compares and contrasts the number of charging stations vs the distances traveled between cities. This is a good example as it presents concise data for the reader to understand, with a good source supporting the data. More explanation could be useful to explain the cost of electric charging versus the gas pump – pros and cons of both- instead of just stating “the picture isn’t perfect”. Add in more sources to back up the costs and a quote from a consumer who has owned an EV and a gas car to compare the experience of traveling long distances. 
